I read the following in the newproducts group and I am obviously
missing something...  While the product sounds interesiting, and we
certainly have an application here where such a device would be very
nice indeed, I don't understand how the system is supposed to work.  The 
thing that confuses me is that the system proports to choose a new
network wide key every 7 seconds (from one of 2^64-1 possable)
RANDOMLY, but without passing any information over the network...  How
can this work?  Also, I wonder how the keys are stored, or rather
since I can't see how they could store such a huge number of keys
large enough to be used as one time pads, are they really xoring with
PSRNs?  Anyway, the thing sounded fishy to me just because if it is
that simple to syncronize security in real time over a reasonably
quick network why do we have all of these slow, complicated systems
like DES?  

Anyway, thanks for your help, and sorry if the questions are really
dumb--I'm quite new to all of this...

-tom


